                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a01">
                      <desc type="GuestText">
                      <locus target="#133v"/> Crude attempt to copy an excerpt <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT1113Anqasa"/>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a02">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#60v"/> note of ownership in a different hand, Qäñazmač Mogäs of Gojjam,
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝዳዊት፡ ዘክቡር፡ ወልዑል፡ መፍቀሬ፡ እግዚአብር፡ ርእሰ፡ መኳንንት፡ ቀኛዝማች፡ ሞገስ፡ ዘምድረ፡ ሙላዱ፡ ጐዣም፡ ዘአጥረዮ፡ በንዋዩ፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ርጉም፡ ከመ፡ ዲያብሎስ፡ ያድርገው፡ አሜን፡</foreign>,
                      “This Dawit belongs to his Excellency, his highness, lover of God, head of princes, Qäazma  Mogäs. His ancestry is from Gojjam. It is purchased with his money. Anyone who steals or erases it, may he be cursed like the devil. Amen.”
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e01">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#19v #22v #35r #37r"/>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#38r"/>);
                      and in the bottom margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#131r"/>, line 7);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#2r #5v #24r #46r"/>, etc.);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#107v #124v"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e02">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#33v"/>, line 12; <locus target="#60r"/>, line 8: text is circled to signal its erasure to correct homoeoteleuton
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e03">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an 
                      appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the
                      scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout).
                      </desc>
                      </item>

